items.basicinformationcomments: Energy Cost Adjustment and Western Units Revenue Sharing Adjustment: Applicable to NET use by customer
items.description: To any residential customer who has onsite renewable generation on the customer side of the meter and single-phase or three-phase service at 60 Hz at a nominal voltage of 120/240 volts or 480 volts furnished through one meter for domestic purposes only including lighting, small domestic appliances, water heating, supplemental space heating, refrigeration, cooking and domestic single phase motors rated 5 HP or less. Service to multiple dwelling units or an apartment house through a single meter is not permitted, except where allowed by Iowa Utilities Board rules.

Period 1: Summer, Period 2: Winter
